1
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 13=

3
00:00:47,260 --> 00:00:48,140
Stop right there.

4
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,500
(Investigation into Yancheng
Opium Addiction Groups)

5
00:00:56,220 --> 00:00:57,379
How did you get

6
00:00:57,380 --> 00:00:59,540
the documents I gave the Commander?

7
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,800
(Investigation into the ships
at Yancheng Port)

8
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:12,560
Commander-in-Chief, are you
referring to this document?

9
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:14,780
It just looks similar.

10
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:18,339
Commander-in-Chief Li,

11
00:01:18,340 --> 00:01:19,420
I've heard so much about you.

12
00:01:19,460 --> 00:01:21,060
Why didn't you introduce us?

13
00:01:21,940 --> 00:01:23,020
My apologies,

14
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:24,420
Commander-in-Chief.

15
00:01:25,380 --> 00:01:27,100
This is my wife, Xue Wan.

16
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:30,740
Didn't I send you to handle something?

17
00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:33,540
I'm sorry.

18
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:37,980
She kept insisting on following me.

19
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:39,700
So...

20
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:41,300
Please don't laugh at us.

21
00:01:43,660 --> 00:01:44,979
Go handle it right away

22
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:46,780
so nothing unexpected happens later.

23
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:47,500
All right.

24
00:01:48,060 --> 00:01:49,060
Go.

25
00:01:51,740 --> 00:01:54,060
Darling, then I'll go
see the Commander-in-Chief off.

26
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:56,840
Commander-in-Chief, this way.

27
00:01:58,420 --> 00:01:59,940
(How does he have)

28
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,940
(the scent of the perfume
from the Fragrance Gala on him?)

29
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:04,900
Every perfume here

30
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:06,820
has a completely unique scent.

31
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:10,260
(This scent...)

32
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:13,060
(How does this scent
end up on Gu Nianchi?)

33
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,700
(This bottle of perfume...)

34
00:02:20,460 --> 00:02:23,220
(I used it on that masked man.)

35
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,060
(Could it be...)

36
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:38,960
Look at me. I'm good.

37
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,520
If you don't believe me,
feel my forehead.

38
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:46,980
It really doesn't seem hot anymore.

39
00:02:49,580 --> 00:02:52,060
Didn't your fever already go down?

40
00:02:52,340 --> 00:02:53,579
The roast chicken is ready.

41
00:02:53,580 --> 00:02:54,780
Come downstairs and eat.

42
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,060
I don't want that.

43
00:02:57,620 --> 00:02:58,740
I want you.

44
00:02:58,820 --> 00:02:59,939
Let go of me!

45
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:01,220
Let go!

46
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:05,180
Xue Wan.

47
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:06,980
Open the door, Xue Wan!

48
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:12,740
Why are you wearing glasses?

49
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,620
Doesn't wearing glasses
during business talks

50
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:17,900
make me seem more composed?

51
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:18,900
Commander.

52
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:20,940
(No wonder.)

53
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:24,260
(I always felt like Gu Nianchi became
a completely different person sometimes.)

54
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:27,300
(Because they were actually
two different people.)

55
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,260
(And I...)

56
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:32,380
(Only realized it now.)

57
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:39,900
(So the one who killed my family
wasn't the real Gu Nianchi.)

58
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:43,340
(From the very beginning,)

59
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,020
(I misunderstood him.)

60
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,420
Commander.

61
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:56,900
She did it on purpose.

62
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:58,100
If there wasn't a scar,

63
00:03:58,260 --> 00:03:59,860
why would she get this tattoo?

64
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:00,579
That's because...

65
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:03,700
Of course it was because I personally
tattooed it on my wife on our wedding night.

66
00:04:04,170 --> 00:04:10,390
♪Fates intertwined,
right and wrong no longer clear♪

67
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,079
♪The world becomes a prison♪

68
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:16,420
♪Even fleeting happiness is enough♪

69
00:04:17,050 --> 00:04:19,469
♪This heart and love slowly fade away♪

70
00:04:19,470 --> 00:04:22,899
♪What kind of ending
will this fate bring?♪

71
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,820
Today, we stand together
beneath the snow.

72
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,189
One day, we'll grow old together.

73
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:29,770
♪Etching our promises
into each other's hearts♪

74
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:31,700
I'm sorry.

75
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:34,100
I came too late.

76
00:04:36,290 --> 00:04:39,239
♪So called blame,
nothing more than an excuse♪

77
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:42,549
♪Where in time did my heart belong?♪

78
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:45,809
♪Even if time has given up on us♪

79
00:04:45,810 --> 00:04:49,040
♪I still long to hold you once again♪

80
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:52,129
♪When love runs deep,
why fear growing old together?♪

81
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:56,200
♪Let the frost wither
the greenery beyond the window♪

82
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:59,019
(And all this time, he's
been silently protecting me.)

83
00:04:59,020 --> 00:05:01,490
♪How can love remain so calm?♪

84
00:05:01,910 --> 00:05:05,119
♪So called blame,
nothing more than an excuse♪

85
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,219
♪Where in time did my heart belong?♪

86
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:10,680
♪Even if time has given up on us♪

87
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,000
(European and American
Dance Star Performing Arts)

88
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,139
Shaoyuan, I've already
followed your orders

89
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:15,699
and set up roadblocks

90
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:16,860
along the route they'll take.

91
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:17,939
If we head there now,

92
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:19,420
we'll definitely arrive before they do.

93
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,859
Replace the opium.

94
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:21,980
The timing is perfect.

95
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:24,020
All right.

96
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:26,739
Shaoyuan, I think your plan

97
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:28,139
is absolutely flawless.

98
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,459
By the time they get there,

99
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:31,560
the opium will already
have been swapped out with fake ones.

100
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,860
This batch of opium is the strongest
evidence of their crimes.

101
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:35,900
Today,

102
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:38,019
can we finally confront
Gu Shaoyan directly

103
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:39,500
and take them all down in one move?

104
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,020
That's right.

105
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:43,300
We're heading to the docks now.

106
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:45,780
Once this is all over,

107
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:49,300
I can finally reunite with Yunqiu.

108
00:05:57,460 --> 00:06:00,099
Why are you only showing up now?
You're already half an hour late.

109
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:00,900
Sorry.

110
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:02,940
Something delayed me.

111
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:05,220
Did you get the evidence?

112
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,460
I found it.

113
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:09,459
That's great. Give it to me now.

114
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:11,220
Tomorrow, I'll publish the report.

115
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:14,060
Then Gu Nianchi's crimes
will be exposed to the whole world.

116
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,620
Xue Wan,

117
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:21,220
can I discuss something with you?

118
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,500
Can you hold off
on publishing the report for now?

119
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:28,660
Wasn't this our agreement?

120
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:31,180
You married him in my place,
found evidence of his crimes,

121
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:33,179
and then we'd bring him down together.

122
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,859
Why are you backing out now?

123
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,499
I'm not saying we shouldn't publish it.

124
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,260
I'm asking if we can

125
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,220
wait a little longer.

126
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:43,100
How much longer?

127
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:44,459
I...

128
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,180
I...

129
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:46,900
I'm not sure.

130
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:48,340
Until...

131
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,379
(If the report gets published now,)

132
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:51,360
(as the stand in,)

133
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,820
(he'll definitely get dragged
into this because of Gu Nianchi.)

134
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,900
(How can I possibly protect both sides?)

135
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:58,379
You're the one who called me yesterday.

136
00:06:58,380 --> 00:06:59,780
I've already prepared the article.

137
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,480
I even had my coworkers finish
the newspaper layout and send it to print.

138
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,940
All we're missing now is the evidence.

139
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:06,220
If the report doesn't go out tomorrow,

140
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,340
everyone at the newspaper office
will laugh at me.

141
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:11,140
At that point, I won't
be able to stay there anymore.

142
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,220
I don't care.

143
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:17,300
By tomorrow night at the latest,
you must give me the evidence.

144
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:18,460
Xue Wan,

145
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,980
I'm truly sorry.

146
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:22,840
But things have changed now.

147
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:25,190
You can't bear to give up your position
as the Commander's wife, can you?

148
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:27,640
Do you really think I'm the kind
of person who chases wealth and status?

149
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:29,179
It's because of the Commander.

150
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:29,739
Actually...

151
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:32,420
I don't think it's the title of
the Commander's wife you can't give up.

152
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,460
It's the Commander himself.

153
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:37,000
You're the one who told me

154
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,659
Gu Nianchi was a despicable man
who committed every evil imaginable,

155
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,099
and told me not to trust him.

156
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,860
So what happened to you now?

157
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,100
Xue Wan,

158
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,419
this situation is complicated.

159
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:48,300
- But it's definitely not what you think.
- Enough.

160
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:50,339
You're the one who came to me back then,

161
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:52,539
saying you knew
I didn't want an arranged marriage,

162
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:55,500
and that you wanted to protect Yancheng
and its people together with me.

163
00:07:55,860 --> 00:07:56,860
And now?

164
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:58,060
Just because of one man,

165
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,179
you've forgotten everything

166
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,100
you said?

167
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:01,660
I haven't forgotten.

168
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:03,339
Xue Wan, trust me.

169
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:05,899
I really just need a little more time
to resolve this.

170
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,339
Save it.

171
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:08,580
Don't forget,

172
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:11,459
you married into the Commander's
Residence using my identity.

173
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:13,980
If I don't see the evidence
by tomorrow night,

174
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,500
I'll tell the Commander

175
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:18,660
that you're not the eldest daughter
of the Xue family at all.

176
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,220
Your name is Zhuang Yunqiu.

177
00:08:20,780 --> 00:08:23,060
Let's see how you'll stay
the Commander's wife then.

178
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:26,860
Xue Wan...

179
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:39,760
Sir.

180
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:45,300
Commander.

181
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:47,820
Did something good happen today?

182
00:08:47,940 --> 00:08:50,300
Tell me so I can share the joy too.

183
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:54,900
Sure.

184
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,820
This is your reward.

185
00:08:58,420 --> 00:08:59,820
Thank you, Commander.

186
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:01,380
Commander.

187
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,579
Commander. Something terrible happened.

188
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:05,979
The deal went through,

189
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:06,660
but...

190
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,700
The goods are fake.

191
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,060
What?

192
00:09:14,780 --> 00:09:15,900
Who did it?

193
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:18,980
We don't know yet.

194
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:29,340
Then what are you still doing here?

195
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,260
Go investigate now.

196
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:34,340
Yes, Sir.

197
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:37,979
Commander.

198
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:39,500
What goods are you talking about?

199
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:41,140
Come drink with me instead.

200
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:42,779
What's wrong with you?

201
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:44,100
Come on, let's drink.

202
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,180
Drink.

203
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:47,299
Drink.

204
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:47,940
You drink.

205
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:48,979
You drink.

206
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,220
All right. I'll drink.

207
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:56,660
I told you to drink,
and you actually did it!

208
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:01,380
Get out, all of you!

209
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:05,020
Move, hurry up and go!

210
00:10:24,420 --> 00:10:25,900
Perfect timing.

211
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,740
You were behind

212
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,660
the opium shipment
at the docks, weren't you?

213
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:33,820
I was.

214
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,020
And not only that.

215
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:39,479
I even prepared this for you.

216
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,160
(Investigation into
Yancheng Opium Addiction Groups)

217
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,020
Shaoyuan,

218
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:56,260
have I not treated you well enough?

219
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:00,940
Whatever you want, I can give it to you.

220
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,100
Gu Nianchi,

221
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:04,380
wasn't the reason you approached me

222
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:07,100
from the very beginning
to make me your scapegoat?

223
00:11:16,390 --> 00:11:21,080
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

224
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:27,710
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

225
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:31,790
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

226
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:35,140
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

227
00:11:35,310 --> 00:11:40,430
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

228
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:46,740
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

229
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:53,400
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

230
00:11:53,940 --> 00:11:57,320
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

231
00:11:57,570 --> 00:12:00,519
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

232
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:05,659
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

233
00:12:05,660 --> 00:12:09,979
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

234
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:12,559
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

235
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:14,839
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

236
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:18,389
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

237
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:22,919
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

238
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:25,450
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

239
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:27,539
♪Still I walk into♪

240
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:31,139
♪The trap you set without regret♪

241
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:35,189
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

242
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:37,769
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

243
00:12:37,770 --> 00:12:39,929
♪A stand in can never cross♪

244
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:43,369
♪The shortest distance between us♪

245
00:12:43,370 --> 00:12:48,340
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

246
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:53,170
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

247
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,519
♪A substitute♪

248
00:12:57,520 --> 00:13:02,520
♪Needs no reason♪

